SOME WR TRAINS AFFECTED DUE TO BLOCK BETWEEN

UMROLI AND BOISAR STATION

In order to carry out the work of shifting/modification of existing overhead line a Traffic cum Power Block will be undertaken between Umroli & Boisar station from 18th to 21st May 2023 similarly, a Traffic cum Power Block will also be undertaken for launching of composite girder of Road over Bridge No. 129 A at Palghar Station o­n 21st May 2023. The block will be taken for a duration of 1 hrs. From 10.05 hrs to 11.05 hrs o­n both UP & DOWN lines between Umroli - Boisar station from 18thto 20th May 2023 and for a duration of 2 hrs. I.e. from 08.45 hrs to 10.45 hrs o­n both UP & DOWN lines between Palghar & Boisar station o­n 21st May, 2023. Due to these blocks, several WR trains will be regulated, short terminated/ partially cancelled.

According to a press release issued by Shri Sumit Thakur, Chief Public Relations Officer of Western Railway, few WR trains will be affected. Details of the trains being affected are as under:

3.Train No. 01338 Dombivli â€“ Boisar MEMU of 21st, May 2023 will be short terminated at Palghar and hence will be partially cancelled between Palghar and Boisar.
